rComments: I enjoyed Professor Lanza's lectures. His accent is hard to understand at first but you get used to it. His slides contained a lot of information, which was helpful when studying for exams. In his class you know what you need to know to pass the course with a good grade.

The course was very disorganized with unclear instructions. the instructor also tests his students on unnecessary, very micro topics and facts, not the big picture. his lectures are also very disorganized, hard to understand. I heard he's very nice when you approach him for help but the course itself was very poorly run

By virtue prof lanza is not a political science professor and has no business teaching a class on modern political thought. Taking his lectures often make me more unsure of the course material, this is further exacerbated by his thick accent which could be compensated by concise lecture slides which are also coincidentally absent. HARD TESTS!

His teaching of political science is poor, disorganised, old and so bad that its almost satirical . He's extremely hard to follow because he'll jump from one point to a completely different one mid sentence, the slides at times make no sense due to their organisation making you do an elaborate tuition paid game of connect the dots.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: I had Dr. Lanza for FRE240. He is a very caring and respected person. The lectures are quite long, so it does get a bit hard to keep paying attention, however his lectures would help you with studying for tests and quizzes. Make sure to have it all jotted down. You must do the readings before going to lectures. Overall a great prof!
He's so sweet! He will help you with anything and is willing to work through any language barriers or other problems you may have! Would highly recommend!
